    "last_activity_date" : 1578058826,
    "last_edit_date" : 1578058826,
    "creation_date" : 1358797072,
    "answer_id" : 14445938,
    "question_id" : 908489,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>I'm adding an answer here in case someone else finds this on Google. Same symptoms; different problem. For me, the type caches had become corrupt.</p>\n\n<p>From <a href=\"http://mschrag.blogspot.co.nz/2009/01/open-type-cant-find-your-class.html\" rel=\"noreferrer\">http://mschrag.blogspot.co.nz/2009/01/open-type-cant-find-your-class.html</a></p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Quit Eclipse</li>\n<li>Go to workspace/.metadata/.plugins/org.eclipse.jdt.core</li>\n<li>Remove *.index and savedIndexNames.txt</li>\n<li>Restart Eclipse and search <kbd>Ctrl</kbd>+<kbd>T</kbd> for the offending type. The indexes will be rebuilt.</li>\n</ul>\n"
  }, {
