    "answer_id" : 20299905,
    "question_id" : 908489,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>None of these worked for me.</p>\n\n<p>I was experiencing this issue in only once particular class.  What finally worked for me was to delete the offending class and recreate it.  Problem solved... mystery not so much!</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 300370,
      "reputation" : 3248,
      "user_id" : 607470,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 64,
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/G5rux.jpg?s=256",
      "display_name" : "Elroy Flynn",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/607470/elroy-flynn"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 7,
    "last_activity_date" : 1580854540,
    "last_edit_date" : 1580854540,
    "creation_date" : 1388550152,
    "answer_id" : 20865501,
    "question_id" : 908489,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>I had this problem and like @Marc, only on a particular class.  I discovered that I needed to designate Open With = Java Editor.  As a Eclipse newbie I hadn't even realized that I was just using a plain text editor.</p>\n\n<p>In the package explorer, right-click the file and chose \"Open With\". </p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 343661,
      "reputation" : 434,
      "user_id" : 1026248,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 50,
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/1cea7a3c5a81da1f60b8c6bf4f63dfd1?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "Aaron",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/1026248/aaron"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 5,
    "last_activity_date" : 1389994894,
    "creation_date" : 1389994894,
    "answer_id" : 21196432,
    "question_id" : 908489,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>Check that you did not filter out many options inside the Window > Preferences > Java > Appearance > Type Filters</p>\n\n<p>Items in this list will not be appear in quick fix, be autocompleted, or appear in other various places like the Open Type dialog.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 3162994,
      "reputation" : 1453,
      "user_id" : 2673577,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 0,
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/978096ff55892d0d390943b6285f7f13?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "asifaftab87",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/2673577/asifaftab87"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 5,
    "last_activity_date" : 1477175905,
    "last_edit_date" : 1477175905,
    "creation_date" : 1410429570,
    "answer_id" : 25784473,
    "question_id" : 908489,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>I also face this issue but it is resolved in different way.\nSteps that I follow may be helpful for others.</p>\n\n<ol>\n<li>Right click on project (the one you are working on)</li>\n<li>Go to Properties > Java Build Path > JRE System Library</li>\n<li>Click Edit... on the right</li>\n<li>Choose the JRE 7</li>\n</ol>\n"
  }, {
