    "last_activity_date" : 1589679480,
    "creation_date" : 1589679480,
    "answer_id" : 61845888,
    "question_id" : 908489,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>Running STS on Java Spring Boot projects, here's what works for me :</p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://i.sstatic.net/OV89f.jpg\" rel=\"noreferrer\"><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/OV89f.jpg\" alt=\"enter image description here\"></a></p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 6679362,
      "reputation" : 1372,
      "user_id" : 5153063,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 60,
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/46bd45e41939e8302319eeeebbf19d8a?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG&f=y&so-version=2",
      "display_name" : "Robert",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/5153063/robert"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 1,
    "last_activity_date" : 1630936542,
    "creation_date" : 1630936542,
    "answer_id" : 69075743,
    "question_id" : 908489,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>For me in Sep 2021 it was an odd Eclipse bug.  I had a multi-line string inside an annotation in my Class.  This caused just that particular class to fail when trying to code complete (even though the class compiled just fine).</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 6833305,
      "reputation" : 3401,
      "user_id" : 5256337,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/d3GFu.jpg?s=256",
      "display_name" : "Lova Chittumuri",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/5256337/lova-chittumuri"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 5,
    "last_activity_date" : 1640496944,
    "creation_date" : 1640496944,
    "answer_id" : 70484422,
    "question_id" : 908489,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>We can change the settings as per our requirement.</p>\n<p>Suppose we want to make <b>java proposal</b> as highest priority we need to do changes as shown below.</p>\n<p><KBD>Windows</KBD> &gt; <KBD>Preferences</KBD> &gt; <KBD>Java</KBD> &gt; <KBD>Editor</KBD> &gt; <KBD>Content Assist</KBD> &gt;<KBD> Advanced</KBD></p>\n<p>Choose <KBD>Java proposal</KBD> and click on <KBD>up</KBD> button</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://i.sstatic.net/sDn9x.jpg\" rel=\"noreferrer\"><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/sDn9x.jpg\" alt=\"enter image description here\" /></a></p>\n"
  } ],
