  "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/questions/908489/eclipse-java-code-completion-not-working",
  "title" : "Eclipse/Java code completion not working",
  "body" : "<p>I've downloaded, unzipped and setup Eclipse 3.4.2 with some plugins (noteable, EPIC, Clearcase, QuantumDB, MisterQ). </p>\n\n<p>Now I find when I'm editing Java projects the code completion is not working.  If I type <code>String.</code> and press <kbd>ctrl</kbd>+<kbd>space</kbd> a popup shows \"No Default Proposals\" and the status bar at the bottom shows \"No completions available\".</p>\n\n<p>Any ideas?</p>\n"
}